   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="transcription">
            <p>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><pc>॥</pc><w>śilabhātriśke</w><w>atätane</w><w>läkāṣi</w><w>tutse</w><w>ṣotri</w><w>läkātär</w><w>paikka</w><pc>॥</pc></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">|| śilabhātriśke saw <hi>atätane</hi>. The sign thereof is seen. He wrote [it]. ||</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="philcomment">The leaf belongs to a Sanskrit manuscript containing āryās from the Upālisūtra of the Madyamāgama; on the verso side of this leaf one has a Sanskrit jagatī praising the donor of the manuscript; see <bibl><title corresp="ref:waldschmidt1971"/><citedRange>124-123</citedRange></bibl>. According to K.T. Schmidt apud <bibl><title corresp="ref:waldschmidt1971"/><citedRange>124-123, fn. 9</citedRange></bibl>, the Tocharian colophon is a "Schreiberzusatz, der in keinem ersichtlichen Zusammenhang mit der vorangehenden Skt.-Strophe steht".</note><note type="remarks">The Sanskrit donor text on the verso side is complete so that it must have been written onto the already damaged leaf, as per Heinrich Lüders apud <bibl><title corresp="ref:waldschmidt1971"/><citedRange>122, fn. 3</citedRange></bibl>. The Tocharian colphon has been written again by a different hand with a brush.</note></p>
         </div>
         <div type="bibliography">
            <p><label>other</label><bibl><title corresp="ref:waldschmidt1965"/><citedRange>121-123</citedRange></bibl> (reading: Klaus T. Schmidt); <bibl><title corresp="ref:malzahn2007b"/><citedRange>303</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            <p><label>Online access</label><bibl><title corresp="ref:idp0000"/><ref target="http://idp.bbaw.de/database/oo_loader.a4d?pm=SHT 872/3" type="external">SHT 872.3</ref></bibl>. </p>
         </div>
